The paper deals with the recognition of sets of words over a rational base, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). The use of first-order logic to characterise these sets suggests a connection to mathematical logic (cs.LO). The study of finite automata and recognisability is also a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper mentions the order relation and modulo operator, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC).
